This paper deals with knowledge graph embedding, which involves representing entities and relations in a continuous space. This is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG), as well as in databases (cs.DB) and natural language processing (cs.CL) where knowledge graphs are often used. The paper also discusses link prediction, which is a task commonly studied in information retrieval (cs.IR).
